Sentencas: NiO-SDC(Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9) cermet anodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were fabricated by sintering NiO-SDC composite particles derived from gel-casting.
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The influence of Ni content and sintering temperature on the electrode polarization using humidified CH4 as fuel was investigated in order to optimize the fabrication conditions.
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The lowest anodic polarization was obtained for an anode sintered at 1350 degrees C and consisting of equal volume of Ni and SDC.
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The anodic polarization at 600 degrees C was about 37 mV at a current density of 300 mA/cm(2).
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Maximum power density of 352 mW/cm(2) was achieved at 600 degrees C for a single cell based on the optimized anode, inferring high catalytic activity of the gel-cast Ni-SDC anode.
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: This high performance seems to be attributed to the microstructure in which Ni and SDC are uniformly distributed.
Titulo: Fabrication of NiO-SDC composite anodes using gel-casting for low-temperature SOFCs
